{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "03", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "06", "M": "16", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "HC directs Haryana government to explain delay in constituting SEIAA after February", "para": "The Punjab and Haryana High Court has ordered the State of Haryana to provide a specific affidavit. This affidavit must clarify why the State Environment Impact Assessment Authority has not been constituted after February 2025. The court also seeks all correspondence between the state and the Union government on this matter.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/high-court-orders-haryana-to-justify-delay-in-seiaa-formation-after-february-2025/125046566?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-11914/125046566.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Real estate companies from other cities flock to NCR on rising demand, prices", "para": "In a surprising turn of events, developers from Mumbai and Bengaluru are setting their sights on the National Capital Region, where property prices are outpacing growth seen elsewhere. Real estate giants are not just launching new projects; they are also significantly enlarging their market footprint.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ncr-real-estate-boom-developers-from-mumbai-and-bengaluru-invest-in-growing-market/125046539?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-386973/125046539.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Register Lucknow development body's properties at special camp from Nov 3-15", "para": "Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is organizing a 13-day 'single-window' camp from November 3-15 to expedite pending property registrations.  LDA officials will prepare documents for the first 10 days, with the registry department finalizing registrations on-site during the last three days. Allottees who have paid in full or 80% or more are being contacted to complete their property registries.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/special-camp-for-lucknow-development-authority-property-registration-from-nov-3-15/125046512?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39394/125046512.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}